<subSubSection lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="449" pageId="51" pageNumber="447" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="51.[136,776,307,363]" lastBlockId="53.[136,775,188,309]" lastPageId="53" lastPageNumber="449" pageId="51" pageNumber="447">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,251,307,331]" pageId="51" pageNumber="447">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Carapace subquadrate, about 1.4 times as broad as long, dorsal surface granulated; regions indistinct, H-shaped depression shallow medially (
<figureCitation box="[1155,1255,190,214]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="51.[136,171,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetId="figure-40@51.[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Fig. 41. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, overall view of carapace, chelipeds and P2–P4; B, ventral view of cephalothorax; C, abdomen and telson; D, chelae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354035/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="447">Fig. 41A</figureCitation>
). Eye small, slightly movable, cornea small, globular, narrower than peduncle, peduncle with scattered granules. Pterygostomial region with row of oblique striae and scattered tubercles. Third maxilliped (
<figureCitation box="[844,952,318,342]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="51.[136,171,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetId="figure-40@51.[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Fig. 41. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, overall view of carapace, chelipeds and P2–P4; B, ventral view of cephalothorax; C, abdomen and telson; D, chelae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354035/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="447">Figs. 41B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[964,1011,318,342]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="52.[113,148,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox="[113,1446,568,1996]" captionTargetId="figure-11@52.[83,1477,522,2010]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Fig. 42. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, dorsolateral margin of carapace; B, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing sternoabdominal cavity and thoracic sternal groove; C, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing thoracic sternal groove and telson; D, left third maxilliped; E, male abdomen and telson; F, G, G1; H, female abdomen and telson. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354037/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="447">42D</figureCitation>
) broad, ischium longer than merus, mesial margin straight; combined length of dactylus, propodus and carpus shorter than that of merus and ischium; exopod narrow, 0.4 width of ischium, flagellum well developed. Chelipeds (
<figureCitation box="[121,218,286,310]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="51.[136,171,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetId="figure-40@51.[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Fig. 41. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, overall view of carapace, chelipeds and P2–P4; B, ventral view of cephalothorax; C, abdomen and telson; D, chelae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354035/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">Fig. 41D</figureCitation>
) stout, unequal; major chela with slight gap when fingers closed, palm slightly wider than long, surface covered with tubercles; minor chela with narrow gap when fingers closed, dorsal surface of palm covered by large tubercles. P2–P4 relatively long (
<figureCitation box="[362,463,414,438]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="51.[136,171,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetId="figure-40@51.[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Fig. 41. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, overall view of carapace, chelipeds and P2–P4; B, ventral view of cephalothorax; C, abdomen and telson; D, chelae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354035/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">Fig. 41A</figureCitation>
); merus of P4 2.8 times as long as broad, shallow longitudinal median groove present; P2 with dactylus upcurved. Male thoracic sternum broad (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="51.[136,171,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetId="figure-40@51.[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Fig. 41. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, overall view of carapace, chelipeds and P2–P4; B, ventral view of cephalothorax; C, abdomen and telson; D, chelae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354035/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">Figs. 41B, C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[210,292,510,534]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="52.[113,148,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox="[113,1446,568,1996]" captionTargetId="figure-11@52.[83,1477,522,2010]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Fig. 42. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, dorsolateral margin of carapace; B, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing sternoabdominal cavity and thoracic sternal groove; C, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing thoracic sternal groove and telson; D, left third maxilliped; E, male abdomen and telson; F, G, G1; H, female abdomen and telson. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354037/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">42B, C</figureCitation>
); sternites 1 and 2 fused, separated from sternite 3 by distinct ridge; sternites 3 and 4 fused; thoracic sternal groove short, extends obliquely from sternoabdominal cavity to middle of sternite 3 (
<figureCitation box="[1154,1264,254,278]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="51.[136,171,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetId="figure-40@51.[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Fig. 41. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, overall view of carapace, chelipeds and P2–P4; B, ventral view of cephalothorax; C, abdomen and telson; D, chelae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354035/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">Figs. 41B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1279,1327,254,278]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="52.[113,148,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox="[113,1446,568,1996]" captionTargetId="figure-11@52.[83,1477,522,2010]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Fig. 42. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, dorsolateral margin of carapace; B, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing sternoabdominal cavity and thoracic sternal groove; C, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing thoracic sternal groove and telson; D, left third maxilliped; E, male abdomen and telson; F, G, G1; H, female abdomen and telson. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354037/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">42B</figureCitation>
); sternite 8 exposed, rectangular, slightly longer than abdominal somite 1; sternoabdominal cavity reaches base of sternite 3. Male abdomen (
<figureCitation box="[925,1033,350,374]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="51.[136,171,2062,2084]" captionTargetBox="[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetId="figure-40@51.[136,1472,390,2031]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Fig. 41. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, overall view of carapace, chelipeds and P2–P4; B, ventral view of cephalothorax; C, abdomen and telson; D, chelae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354035" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354035/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">Figs. 41C</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1045,1089,350,374]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="52.[113,148,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox="[113,1446,568,1996]" captionTargetId="figure-11@52.[83,1477,522,2010]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Fig. 42. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, dorsolateral margin of carapace; B, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing sternoabdominal cavity and thoracic sternal groove; C, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing thoracic sternal groove and telson; D, left third maxilliped; E, male abdomen and telson; F, G, G1; H, female abdomen and telson. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354037/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">42E</figureCitation>
) relatively narrow; somites 1 and 2 free, somites 3–5 fused, lateral margin sinuous; somite 6 slightly shorter than length of somites 3–5, lateral margin expanded medially into blunt triangular projection; telson almost as long as somite 6, distal margin rounded, margin setose. G1 (
<figureCitation box="[943,1071,510,534]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="52.[113,148,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox="[113,1446,568,1996]" captionTargetId="figure-11@52.[83,1477,522,2010]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Fig. 42. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, dorsolateral margin of carapace; B, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing sternoabdominal cavity and thoracic sternal groove; C, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing thoracic sternal groove and telson; D, left third maxilliped; E, male abdomen and telson; F, G, G1; H, female abdomen and telson. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354037/files/figure.png" pageId="52" pageNumber="448">Fig. 42F, G</figureCitation>
) slender, slightly S-shaped, sparse short setae on mesial and lateral margins; distal part tapered, not concealed under abdomen, exposed on thoracic sternal groove, obscured by setae of telson. Female abdomen relatively narrow, with 6 free somites and telson (
