<figureCitation box="[672,762,380,405]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[136,171,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[136,1474,472,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-7@3.[136,1474,472,1864]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Colours in life. A, Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114), Oura Bay, Okinawa Island, Japan; B, Mariaplax ourabay, new species, paratype female (9.2 × 7.0 mm) (ZRC 2012.1032), Oura Bay, Okinawa Island, Japan; C, Mariaplax narusei, new species, holotype male (9.6 × 5.8 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2112), Funaura Bay, Iriomote Island, Japan; D, Rayapinus maenosonoi, new species, holotype male (6.6 × 4.9 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2115) Sesoko, Okinawa, Japan; E, Hexaplax megalops Doflein, 1904, male, (13.5 × 9.0 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-1026), west of New Hanover; F, Hexaplax aurantium, new species, paratype male (12.1 × 8.4 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-1527), south of Lae, Gulf of Huon; G, Hexaplax saudade, new species, paratype male (16.9 × 9.8 mm) (ZRC 2013.1692), AURORA, 2007, station CP2658, Philippines; H, Hexaplax saudade, new species, male (15.9 × 11.1 mm) (ZRC 2008.1456), Su-Ao fish port, Ilan province, Taiwan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5353949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5353949/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
). Female lighter coloured than male (
<figureCitation box="[526,610,412,437]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[136,171,1890,1912]" captionTargetBox="[136,1474,472,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-7@3.[136,1474,472,1864]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 2. Colours in life. A, Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114), Oura Bay, Okinawa Island, Japan; B, Mariaplax ourabay, new species, paratype female (9.2 × 7.0 mm) (ZRC 2012.1032), Oura Bay, Okinawa Island, Japan; C, Mariaplax narusei, new species, holotype male (9.6 × 5.8 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2112), Funaura Bay, Iriomote Island, Japan; D, Rayapinus maenosonoi, new species, holotype male (6.6 × 4.9 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2115) Sesoko, Okinawa, Japan; E, Hexaplax megalops Doflein, 1904, male, (13.5 × 9.0 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-1026), west of New Hanover; F, Hexaplax aurantium, new species, paratype male (12.1 × 8.4 mm) (MNHN-IU-2011-1527), south of Lae, Gulf of Huon; G, Hexaplax saudade, new species, paratype male (16.9 × 9.8 mm) (ZRC 2013.1692), AURORA, 2007, station CP2658, Philippines; H, Hexaplax saudade, new species, male (15.9 × 11.1 mm) (ZRC 2008.1456), Su-Ao fish port, Ilan province, Taiwan." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5353949" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5353949/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
