<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="449" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="53.[136,774,476,532]" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,261,477,501]" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after the 
<typeStatus box="[437,482,477,501]" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">type</typeStatus>
locality Oura Bay, 
<collectingRegion box="[679,774,476,500]" country="Japan" name="Okinawa" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Okinawa</collectingRegion>
Islands, 
<collectingCountry box="[227,291,509,532]" name="Japan" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Japan</collectingCountry>
. The name is used as a noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="449" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[136,775,572,885]" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,250,573,597]" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male telson of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rahayu &amp; Ng, 2014" authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2014" box="[490,710,572,596]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Mariaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ourabay" status="new species">
<emphasis box="[490,710,572,596]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Mariaplax ourabay</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="53" pageNumber="449" rank="species">new species</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is almost as long as the sixth abdominal somite, a characters shared only with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Campbell &amp; Stephenson" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[450,611,636,660]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Mariaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulifera">
<emphasis box="[450,611,636,660]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">M. granulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the male abdomen of these two species differs in the length proportion of the somite 6 to that of the somites 3–5 (
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="53" pageNumber="449" unit="in" value="0.6">0.6 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2014" box="[166,293,732,756]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Mariaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ourabay">
<emphasis box="[166,293,732,756]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">M. ourabay</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
versus 
<quantity box="[378,442,732,757]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.032" pageId="53" pageNumber="449" unit="in" value="0.8">0.8 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Campbell &amp; Stephenson" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[450,609,732,756]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Mariaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulifera">
<emphasis box="[450,609,732,756]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">M. granulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Furthermore, the G1 structures of these two species differ markedly: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2014" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Mariaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ourabay">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">M. ourabay</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has long, slender G1 with a pointed tip (
<figureCitation captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="52.[113,148,2034,2056]" captionTargetBox="[113,1446,568,1996]" captionTargetId="figure-11@52.[83,1477,522,2010]" captionTargetPageId="52" captionText="Fig. 42. Mariaplax ourabay, new species, holotype male (7.6 × 5.4 mm) (RUMF-ZC-2114). A, dorsolateral margin of carapace; B, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing sternoabdominal cavity and thoracic sternal groove; C, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing thoracic sternal groove and telson; D, left third maxilliped; E, male abdomen and telson; F, G, G1; H, female abdomen and telson. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354037" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354037/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Fig. 42F, G</figureCitation>
) while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rahayu &amp; Ng" authorityYear="2014" baseAuthorityName="Campbell &amp; Stephenson" baseAuthorityYear="1970" box="[269,427,828,852]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hexapodidae" genus="Mariaplax" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="53" pageNumber="449" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulifera">
<emphasis box="[269,427,828,852]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">M. granulifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the G1 is stout and proximally much wider than the tip (
<figureCitation box="[414,530,860,885]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="45.[136,171,2005,2027]" captionTargetBox="[155,1447,191,1959]" captionTargetId="figure-6@45.[146,1461,166,1977]" captionTargetPageId="45" captionText="Fig. 36. Mariaplax granulifera (Campbell &amp;Stephenson, 1970), male (6.2 × 4.5 mm) (QM-W8299). A, dorsolateral margin of carapace; B, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing sternoabdominal cavity and thoracic sternal groove; C, thoracic sternites 1–5, showing thoracic sternal groove and telson; D, male abdomen and telson; E, left third maxilliped; F, major chela; G, minor chela; H, left P4; I, J, G1. Scale bars = 1.0 mm" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5354023" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5354023/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="449">Fig. 36I, J</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
